{{Infobox NRHP | name = Bend Amateur Athletic Club Gymnasium | nrhp_type = | image = Bend Amateur Athletic Club Gymnasium - Bend Oregon.jpg | caption = | location = 547 Wall Street, [[Bend, Oregon]] | coordinates = {{coord|44|3|23|N|121|18|54|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = USA Oregon Bend#USA Oregon | built = 1917 | architect = [[Lee Arden Thomas]] | architecture = Colonial, Jacobean | added = November 25, 1983<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2009a}}</ref> | governing_body = Local | mpsub = {{NRHP url|id=64500507|title=Historic Development of the Bend Company in Bend, Oregon MPS}} | refnum = 83004165 }} The '''Bend Amateur Athletic Club Gymnasium''' is a historic building in [[Bend, Oregon|Bend]], [[Oregon]], United States. It was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] (NRHP) in 1983. The building was designed by [[Lee Arden Thomas]] and built by Guy H. Wilson.
When the Bend School Board established a building committee to develop plans for a new high school in 1923, they followed recommendations from the building committee and accepted the Bend Amateur Athletic Club building from the Bend Holding Company to use as the high school's [[gym]]nasium.<ref name="NR2">[http://www.ci.bend.or.us/depts/community_development/planning_division/docs/historic/Bend_High_School.pdf "Bend High School"], ''National Register of Historic Places Registration Form'', National Park Service, United States Department of Interior, Deschutes County, Oregon, July 23, 1993.</ref> The school would become [[Old Bend High School]] (also listed on the NRHP).
