{{Infobox football association | Logo = Logo_of_Futsal_Association_of_India_(FAI).jpg | sport = Futsal | Founded = 2008 | Folded = | Headquarters = Mumbai, India | Region = | Region affiliation = | Subregion = AMF | Subregion affiliation = 2011 | President = Namdev Shirgaonkar (2014-Present) | Vice-President = | Website = {{URL|http://www.futsalindia.com/}} }}
'''Futsal Association of India''' (FAI) is an organisation which has been developing the game of [[futsal]] ({{IPA-pt|futˈsaw}}) in [[India]] since 2008.
[[Namdev Shirgaonkar]], founder President of FAI, introduced this game in [[India]] in 2007. Since then this game has emerged as new and fast form of [[football]] in India. FAI has been developing futsal through various District, State and National Championships. FAI organised its 1st Youth Futsal Championship in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Futsal scores in popularity|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/futsal-scores-in-popularity/article3070640.ece|website=The Hindu|publisher=The Hindu|accessdate=21 September 2014|date=5 September 2006}}</ref>
FAI is affiliated with [[Asociación Mundial de Fútbol de Salón]] (AMF) since 2011 & is also a founder member of the [[Confederation of Asian Futsal]] (CAFS).<ref>{{cite web|title=Confederation of Asian Futsal|url=http://www.cafs.asia/|website=Confederation of Asian Futsal|publisher=Confederation of Asian Futsal}}</ref>
