{{notability|Sport|date=May 2015}} {{Infobox stadium | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | caption = | stadium_name = Wind-Del Velodrome | fullname = | nickname = | location = 3178 Regional Rd 25, Windham Centre, ON | coordinates = {{Coord|42.910266|N|80.4202200|W|region:CA-ON_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | owner = | built = 1972 | opened = | cost = | seating_capacity = | tenants = | dimensions = 250 meter oval }}
The '''Wind-Del Velodrome''' is a 250m outdoor bicycle racing track located in Windham Centre, Ontario, and is one of only three velodromes in the province.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.yorkregion.com/news-story/1427412-vaughan-may-get-back-in-on-pan-am-games-action/|title = Vaughan may get back in on Pan Am Games action|date = Oct 21, 2011|accessdate = 14 August 2015|website = York Region.com|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> The surface is asphalt, and the corners are banked 13 degrees.<ref>{{cite web|title=It's the racing that counts, not the track|url=http://cycle-wire.com/its-the-racing-that-counts-not-the-track/|website=Cycle Wire|publisher=Cycle Wire|accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref> It was constructed in 1972 by Belgian immigrants to the area.<ref>{{cite web|title=Delhi, Ont. velodrome faces the end|url=http://cyclingmagazine.ca/sections/news/delhi-ont-velodrome-faces-the-end/|website=Canadian Cycling Magazine|publisher=Canadian Cycling Magazine|accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref> Though the track is not often used, funds for demolition are not available.<ref>{{cite web|title=End of line in sight for velodrome|url=http://www.delhinewsrecord.com/2013/11/11/end-of-the-line-in-sight-for-velodrome|website=Delhi News Record|publisher=Delhi News Record|accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref> In addition to hosting the 2001 Ontario Provincial Track Championships, it has been used as an amphitheater and host for recumbent bicycle races.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ontario Cycling Association Track Racing Results -Provincial Track Championships|url=http://www.canadiancyclist.com/dailynews.php?id=4151|website=Canadian Cyclist Magazine|publisher=Canadian Cyclist|accessdate=14 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Pearce|first1=Daniel R.|title=Wind-Del Velodrome becomes theatre|url=http://www.simcoereformer.ca/2009/07/14/wind-del-velodrome-becomes-theatre|website=Simcoe Reformer|publisher=Simcoe Reformer|accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=WinDel Park|url=http://www.hptabrant.ca/windel.htm|website=Human Powered Transportation Association|publisher=Human Powered Transportation Association|accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref> With the opening of the [[Mattamy National Cycling Center]] in [[Milton, Ontario]], proposals have been made to upgrade the Win-Del Velodrome and use it as a training facility.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Symon|first1=John|title=Wind-Del Velodrome to Become a Training Facility|url=http://pedalmag.com/wind-del-velodrome-to-become-a-training-facility/|website=Pedal Magazine|publisher=Pedal Magazine|accessdate=14 August 2015}}</ref>
